<i>making it difficult to connect
with the crowd.</i>

79
00:05:32,765 --> 00:05:35,435
<i>How will they build unity
with the audience?</i>

80
00:05:38,705 --> 00:05:42,575
<i>Matsumoto draws upon his experience
to give them advice.</i>

81
00:05:43,476 --> 00:05:45,978
Some of you can go in,
then come back on stage.

82
00:05:46,045 --> 00:05:47,513
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

83
00:05:48,114 --> 00:05:51,451
Just enjoy yourself and have a blast.

84
00:05:51,517 --> 00:05:54,520
When you're feeling it,
it will catch on with the audience, too.

85
00:05:54,587 --> 00:05:56,789
-The stage will become friendlier.
-Yes, sir.

86
00:05:57,023 --> 00:06:00,059
Thank you for the advice.

87
00:06:02,428 --> 00:06:07,133
<i>He teaches them
that the most important thing is passion.</i>

88
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:16,175
<i>It is time for them to take the stage.</i>

89
00:06:18,444 --> 00:06:23,015
<i>Some amateur musicians perform
and set the tone.</i>

90
00:06:31,724 --> 00:06:35,261
<i>Bi Shonen must prove their worth
as professionals.</i>

91
00:06:39,799 --> 00:06:40,933
<i>It's time.</i>

92
00:06:48,274 --> 00:06:51,310
<i>The performance begins
as their senior watches over them.</i>

93
00:06:59,552 --> 00:07:02,889
<i>First, they surprise the audience
with a quick costume change.</i>

94
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:09,862
{\an8}<i>Next, a performance with hand fans.</i>

95
00:07:14,767 --> 00:07:16,202
<i>They manage to pull it off.</i>

96
00:07:22,809 --> 00:07:24,377
<i>The opening goes perfectly.</i>

97
00:07:37,890 --> 00:07:40,660
<i>They use Johnny's hit songs
to work up the audience.</i>

98
00:07:50,736 --> 00:07:54,674
<i>Still, they do not feel a connection
with the audience.</i>

99
00:07:57,777 --> 00:08:01,881
<i>The members take their senior's advice
and join the audience.</i>

100
