<i>Much of the American crowd
have never heard of Bi Shonen before.</i>

101
00:08:16,062 --> 00:08:19,465
<i>The finale is Bi Shonen's original song.</i>

102
00:08:20,733 --> 00:08:21,667
<i>That's when...</i>

103
00:08:23,970 --> 00:08:26,906
Come on!

104
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:44,757
{\an8}A BI SHONEN ORIGINAL SONG

105
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:11,951
<i>Even if you don't speak their language</i>

106
00:09:12,018 --> 00:09:15,388
<i>if there is passion,
people will understand.</i>

107
00:09:15,454 --> 00:09:17,757
Bi Shonen!

108
00:09:19,725 --> 00:09:21,427
I had such a blast!

109
00:09:21,494 --> 00:09:22,328
Whoa.

110
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:24,564
I love the audience here.

111
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:25,798
It's so different.

112
00:09:25,865 --> 00:09:27,400
Incredible.

113
00:09:30,069 --> 00:09:31,637
<i>Their next performance is tomorrow.</i>

114
00:09:33,372 --> 00:09:35,207
Oh, this is scarier than I thought.

115
00:09:35,274 --> 00:09:38,644
<i>The members go sightseeing
as part of an interview.</i>

116
00:09:40,346 --> 00:09:41,881
Whoa!

117
00:09:43,883 --> 00:09:45,585
{\an8}MAGAZINE PHOTO SHOOT

118
00:09:45,651 --> 00:09:46,652
{\an8}One, two!

119
00:09:46,719 --> 00:09:49,922
{\an8}<i>The members spend their days shuttling
between work and practice.</i>

120
00:09:50,289 --> 00:09:54,427
<i>They fight immense pressure
before performances.</i>

121
00:09:56,329 --> 00:09:59,966
<i>However, they are no different
from your average teenager.</i>

122
00:10:01,367 --> 00:10:04,437
This is plain chocolate and strawberry.

123
00:10:04,503 --> 00:10:05,605
They have strawberry.

124
00:10:05,671 --> 00:10:06,672
Here.

125
00:10:07,139 --> 00:10:09,008
It's so good!

126
00:10:09,742 --> 00:10:10,710
Thank you.

127
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:15,514
{\an8}<i>Why was Bi Shonen chosen
to perform at Nisei Week?</i>

128
00:10:15,581 --> 00:10:18,117
{\an8}<i>It all started with Iwasaki.</i>

129
00:10:22,855 --> 00:10:25,992
I told Mr. Johnny that

130
00:10:26,058 --> 00:10:30,730
I wanted to study showmanship
and eventually visit the United States.

131
00:10:30,796 --> 00:10:32,565
Mr. Johnny thought it was hilarious.

132
00:10:32,832 --> 00:10:35,735
He was like, "Are you kidding?"

133
00:10:36,002 --> 00:10:40,006
He then told me to hold on
and started checking the schedule.

134
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,375
He said, "Okay.

135
00:10:42,441 --> 00:10:44,944
If you guys want to go, let's go.

136
00:10:45,211 --> 00:10:47,980
But you better give it
your very best shot."

137
00:10:48,848 --> 00:10:51,517
<i>The schedule he checked back then</i>

138
00:10:51,684 --> 00:10:54,720
<i>was for the Nisei Week Festival.</i>

139
00:10:58,290 --> 00:11:01,961
{\an8}<i>Nisei Week began in 1934.</i>

140
00:11:02,028 --> 00:11:05,197
{\an8}<i>He spent his late teens
to twenties in America.</i>

141
00:11:05,264 --> 00:11:06,899
{\an8}<i>The festival was dear to him.</i>

142
00:11:10,703 --> 00:11:11,637
{\an8}LITTLE TOKYO, 1930s

143
00:11:11,704 --> 00:11:14,874
{\an8}<i>The Japanese who migrated
to the United States</i>

144
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:17,243
{\an8}<i>faced unimaginable hardships.</i>

145
00:11:17,309 --> 00:11:19,612
{\an8}<i>Still, they took root in this land.</i>

146
00:11:20,646 --> 00:11:25,151
{\an8}<i>Nisei Week became a point of foundation
for such Japanese immigrants.</i>

147
00:11:26,118 --> 00:11:28,320
{\an8}<i>The festival was filled</i>

148
00:11:28,387 --> 00:11:31,891
{\an8}<i>with the roots of entertainment
such as song and dance</i>

149
00:11:32,091 --> 00:11:34,393
{\an8}<i>which gave people comfort.</i>

150
00:11:34,460 --> 00:11:37,830
{\an8}NISEI WEEK PARADE, 1937

151
00:11:40,066 --> 00:11:42,234
{\an8}<i>The stage Bi Shonen will perform on today</i>

152
00:11:42,301 --> 00:11:46,205
{\an8}<i>is the same stage that the Nisei Week
was held on in the 1930s.</i>

153
00:11:46,272 --> 00:11:48,207
{\an8}KOYASAN BEIKOKU BETSUIN

154
00:11:48,274 --> 00:11:50,710
{\an8}<i>Koyasan Betsuin.</i>

155
00:11:52,211 --> 00:11:54,346
Hello. We're Bi Shonen.

156
00:11:54,613 --> 00:11:58,784
<i>This temple is the family home
that he grew up in.</i>

157
00:12:00,653 --> 00:12:03,589
<i>When his father worked
as the temple monk here,</i>

158
00:12:04,190 --> 00:12:05,958
<i>many immigrants gathered.</i>

159
00:12:07,660 --> 00:12:11,831
<i>And a stage was built
for temple-goers for entertainment</i>

160
00:12:11,897 --> 00:12:13,899
<i>and as a place
to reminisce about their homeland.</i>

161
00:12:17,236 --> 00:12:21,540
<i>The members seem emotional,
standing on the stage where it all began.</i>

162
00:12:23,509 --> 00:12:25,344
He lived here as a child?

163
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:26,312
Yep.

164
00:12:26,879 --> 00:12:28,013
Incredible.

165
00:12:28,247 --> 00:12:30,649
I feel that we mustn't taint

166
00:12:31,317 --> 00:12:34,353
what Mr. Johnny
and his father have built from here.

167
00:12:34,687 --> 00:12:39,492
I want to pay the utmost respect
to the things and people here.

168
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:48,033
<i>Nasu will be speaking in English on stage.
He seems nervous.</i>

169
00:12:53,372 --> 00:12:57,143
<i>Iwasaki seems even more serious.</i>

170
00:12:57,877 --> 00:13:01,914
<i>He was preparing
to sing the Hibari Misora's songs</i>

171
00:13:02,281 --> 00:13:05,384
<i>that were recommended to him.</i>

172
00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:15,261
{\an8}<i>Hibari Misora had actally come to
the United States as a child</i>

173
00:13:15,694 --> 00:13:18,297
{\an8}<i>and sang on this temple's stage
as part of a tour.</i>

174
00:13:19,398 --> 00:13:22,768
{\an8}<i>The man that helped in the production
of that tour</i>

175
00:13:25,504 --> 00:13:28,674
<i>was none other than
the man who helped them.</i>

176
00:13:36,182 --> 00:13:37,716
<i>It's time for rehearsal.</i>

177
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:41,320
Are we ready?

178
00:13:41,921 --> 00:13:42,788
Yep.

179
00:13:42,855 --> 00:13:45,791
Sound check for Taisho.

180
00:13:45,858 --> 00:13:47,193
Thank you.

181
00:13:47,259 --> 00:13:48,861
-Go ahead.
-Okay.

182
00:14:02,908 --> 00:14:05,244
Okay. Thank you.

183
00:14:08,147 --> 00:14:10,182
<i>He doesn't seem happy.</i>

184
00:14:10,916 --> 00:14:13,085
Can you make the music less loud?

185
00:14:13,152 --> 00:14:15,287
Lower the music, please.

186
00:14:18,290 --> 00:14:19,291
<i>One more time.</i>

187
00:14:30,169 --> 00:14:34,206
<i>He sings a few times more,
but is still not happy.</i>

188
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:40,412
So sorry to bother you so many times.

189
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:44,617
Can we let Taisho Iwasaki sing
"Ai San San" once more?

190
00:14:44,683 --> 00:14:46,385
Sorry. One more time.

191
00:14:55,394 --> 00:14:56,662
<i>This is his seventh try.</i>

192
00:15:09,108 --> 00:15:13,979
Sorry. Can we do a sound check
for "Ai San San" one more time?

193
00:15:14,179 --> 00:15:18,717
Why did you sound check that song
so many times?

194
00:15:18,784 --> 00:15:20,920
I guess...

195
00:15:20,986 --> 00:15:24,556
This is a different environment
from usual.

196
00:15:24,790 --> 00:15:28,427
I wanted to practice thoroughly
to perform my best.

197
00:15:28,494 --> 00:15:32,998
That's why I couldn't give up
on practicing.

198
00:15:33,999 --> 00:15:35,267
I want to make sure...

199
00:15:36,902 --> 00:15:38,604
that Mr. Johnny can hear me.

200
00:15:40,406 --> 00:15:42,141
That's what I hope for.

201
00:15:43,776 --> 00:15:46,946
<i>That man taught them
to always give their best effort.</i>

202
00:15:48,647 --> 00:15:50,015
<i>The show is about to start.</i>

203
00:15:51,583 --> 00:15:53,485
{\an8}AUGUST 11
THANK YOU, KOYASAN

204
00:15:53,552 --> 00:15:55,454
{\an8}<i>They are counting down the seconds.</i>

205
00:15:59,091 --> 00:16:02,061
{\an8}<i>Iwasaki's song is the first act.</i>

206
00:16:05,164 --> 00:16:06,131
Will I be able to sing?

207
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:09,068
You know you can sing.

208
00:16:09,134 --> 00:16:12,705
No, I can't. I'm so scared.

209
00:16:28,921 --> 00:16:30,990
<i>First, Nasu addresses the audience.</i>

210
00:16:47,706 --> 00:16:49,742
-Come on!
-You can do this!

211
00:16:59,151 --> 00:17:00,419
<i>The show begins.</i>

212
00:18:00,612 --> 00:18:02,748
<i>Iwasaki has sung this song
for over a year now.</i>

213
00:18:03,182 --> 00:18:07,086
<i>He says that recently he has come
to understand something important.</i>

214
00:18:16,962 --> 00:18:20,232
In the beginning,
I only thought about singing well.

215
00:18:20,299 --> 00:18:23,869
Now, I want my songs
to touch people's hearts.

216
00:18:24,403 --> 00:18:29,374
I want to convey to them
what I'm feeling inside.

217
00:18:37,683 --> 00:18:41,120
{\an8}<i>The members sing hit songs
created by that special someone</i>

218
00:18:41,587 --> 00:18:44,523
<i>like they are carving them
into the stage where it all began.</i>

219
00:19:30,702 --> 00:19:32,638
<i>A look of accomplishment
is on their faces.</i>

220
00:19:33,105 --> 00:19:35,807
They know that they have done their best.

221
00:19:41,547 --> 00:19:44,516
<i>What does Iwasaki think
of his performance?</i>

222
00:19:45,450 --> 00:19:48,120
I'd give me a two.

223
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:49,454
Really?

224
00:19:52,324 --> 00:19:54,526
It's not easy to score full marks.

225
00:19:54,593 --> 00:19:55,994
You're right.

226
00:19:56,628 --> 00:19:57,996
This is what counts.

227
00:19:59,598 --> 00:20:02,100
I need to work on it. I don't have it yet.

228
00:20:03,702 --> 00:20:06,705
Everyone loved the show.

229
00:20:06,772 --> 00:20:09,007
The locals came to me
and congratulated me.

230
00:20:09,074 --> 00:20:11,343
You did fine. They felt you.

231
00:20:14,279 --> 00:20:17,416
<i>It is time to head
